SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 836
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to commend the Nehemiah Alliance and the
National 52 Day Rebuild Initiative and to
encourage the people of Tennessee to lead the
way in this national extended time of prayer,
fasting, repentance, and spiritual renewal during
America's 250th Anniversary.
WHEREAS, the Nehemiah Alliance has launched a historic National 52 Day Rebuild
Initiative, calling the people of the United States to an extended time of unified prayer, fasting,
and repentance for the purpose of rebuilding the spiritual walls of blessing and protection
around our fifty states and our nation; and
WHEREAS, recognizing Tennessee's leadership role in inspiring this now National
Initiative, we call upon Tennesseans to join the Nehemiah Alliance and participate in this historic
National 52 Day Rebuild Initiative; and
WHEREAS, from its founding, the United States of America has been shaped by
enduring Judeo-Christian principles of faith, liberty, and justice and has long understood itself to
be One Nation under God, and throughout our history Americans have turned to these
principles in moments of challenge, seeking renewal, unity, and moral clarity; and
WHEREAS, the Nehemiah Alliance draws inspiration from the biblical account of
Nehemiah, who, with the favor of Heaven, the authorization of government, and the cooperation
of leaders, rebuilt the broken walls of Jerusalem in fifty-two days, and in that same spirit, during
America's two-hundred-fiftieth anniversary, this 52 Day Initiative calls Americans to recognize
that the moral, cultural, and spiritual foundations of our society require our attention and action;
and
WHEREAS, beginning at sundown on September 10, 2026, and concluding at sundown
on All Saints' Sunday, November 1, 2026, this initiative invites people across our nation to
SJR0836
013420
- 1 -

humble themselves before Almighty God through prayer, repentance, and periods of fasting as
each person is individually led; and
WHEREAS, the purpose is to rebuild our walls, restore our homes, revive our hearts,
and renew liberty and justice for all, reunifying us as One Nation under God; and
WHEREAS, the mission of the Nehemiah Alliance is grounded in the call of Scripture,
including the promise recorded in Second Chronicles 7:14, that as His people pray, call upon
His Name, and repent of our sins and those of our nation, God will hear from Heaven and heal
our land; and
WHEREAS, the Alliance seeks to reflect the Body of Christ by bringing together leaders,
pastors, organizations, and intercessors across denominations, ethnicities, and spheres of
influence; and
WHEREAS, participants are encouraged to serve as modern day gatekeepers, building
the wall in front of their own homes and interceding for their families, neighborhoods, schools,
churches, businesses, and all leaders in authority, in accordance with I Timothy 2:1 and 2; and
WHEREAS, drawing from historical precedent, including General George S. Patton's
commissioning of a common prayer for all his troops preceding victory in World War II,
participants will unite in one voice throughout the Initiative to intercede using the "United Prayer
for America"; and
WHEREAS, during the fifty-two days, focused prayers will be made for spheres of
culture, the fifty states and territories, the nation's capital, Congress, the Supreme Court, the
President, his Administration, and the consequential midterm elections; and
WHEREAS, on Saturday, October 31, and All Saints' Sunday, November 1, 2026,
people of faith from across the nation will gather online and in person, including in Washington,
D.C., on the National Mall, in sacred assembly to pray, fast, repent, and stand; now, therefore,
- 2 - 013420

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we recognize and commend the Nehemiah Alliance
for its leadership in advancing the historic National 52 Day Rebuild Initiative.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we encourage the people of Tennessee to lead the
way by joining the Nehemiah Alliance by signing up at www.na52.org and participating in this
solemn and hopeful call to prayer, fasting, and repentance, beginning at sundown on
September 10, 2026, and concluding at sundown on All Saints' Sunday, November 1, 2026.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we honor Tennessee's leadership role in establishing
thirty days of prayer, fasting, and repentance each July and acknowledge its influence in
inspiring this now nationwide initiative.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
